These are the cutest little turkeys 🦃 you have ever seen or eaten! We make these every year for Thanksgiving! 🦃
Use our crescent roll recipe to make these without Kamut. Or use our Kamut roll recipe and use all purpose flour instead of Kamut. 🍁
Make sure to let the dough rise in muffin tins until double. Then bake for 5 minutes on the middle rack and 5 minutes on the lower rack. 
To freeze rolls for Thanksgiving place baked rolls in Freezer bags. Unthaw the morning of Thanksgiving  and carefully wrap in aluminum foil bundles and reheat at 350 degrees until warm. 🦃💫🌟

*Use about 1 cup less flour for Crescent roll recipe using Kamut. 
Use about 1 cup more all purpose flour if using our Kamut roll recipe.

CRESCENT DINNER ROLLS

Makes: 24 rolls
Time 3-4 hours

2 Tablespoons active dry yeast
¼ cup plus 1 Tablespoon warm
(105-115°) water
1 cup milk
3 eggs
½ cup sugar
½ cup canola oil
About 5½ cups all-purpose
flour, divided 4-1/2 Kamut 
2 teaspoons salt
Butter

1. In a small bowl combine the yeast and water.
Cover and let the mixture bloom about 10 min.
2. Meanwhile, heat the milk in the microwave
until just warm, not scalding, 1 min. 45 sec.
3. In a large bowl, beat the eggs, sugar and oil
with a whisk. Stir in the milk and yeast mixture.
With a wooden spoon stir in 4-5 cups of the
flour and salt until combined.
4. Cover with plastic wrap sprayed with cooking
oil and let dough rise in a warm place, 2 to 3
hours.
5. Lightly grease a 12 x 18-inch sheet pan and
set aside.
6. Punch the sticky dough down and turn it onto
a lightly floured surface. Pat it with additional
flour if necessary for handling and keep your
hands floured.
7. Divide the dough into thirds. Roll one section
into a circle about the size of a dinner plate.
With a pizza cutter, cut once down the middle,
then across, then diagonally (the same way a
pizza is cut) to make eight wedges. Roll up
each wedge from the wide end toward the
point. Place the rolls point side down on the
prepared pan. Repeat with the remaining
sections. (All rolls should fit on one sheet pan.)
8. Cover with a clean dishtowel and let rise until
doubled in bulk, about 15 min. Then bake ❌⭕️

This is better than any apple pie !!!! You are going to be obsessed with this recipe 😋😋😋😋😋 you can’t even believe how yummy !!! 
Too with whipped cream or ice cream or both ! Of course I’m using fannies whipped cream ✨🐮 Make and enjoy !!!

HOLLAND’S APPLE TARTE

SERVES 8 | TIME 2 hrs 45 mins  I BAKE 325˚

DOUGH
1 cup (2 sticks) butter, cold
1 cup sugar 
1 egg 
1 teaspoon lemon extract 
1¼ cups White Kamut flour 

Filling 
8 apples (we use honey crisp) peeled, sliced 
¾ cup sugar 
1 Tablespoon cinnamon 
2 teaspoons fresh lemon juice 
1 Tablespoon White Kamut flour 
¹⁄₈ teaspoon Fleur de sel salt 
¾ cup golden raisins (optional) 

1.	In a large bowl, cream together cold butter (cut into chunks) and sugar using a hand-held or electric mixer. Beat in egg and lemon extract. Add flour. Mix well. Dough will be very soft. Cover and place in refrigerator while preparing filling (about 20 minutes). 
2.	Prepare the filling: Peel and thinly slice apples. Place in a large bowl. Add sugar, cinnamon, lemon juice, salt and flour. Mix well. (If using raisins, place in a strainer and wash with hot water, then add to the apple mixture.) Set aside and let sit for 20 minutes. 
3.	Preheat oven to 325º. Remove dough from refrigerator. Use ¾ of dough for the bottom and up the sides of the spring form pan. Use remaining dough for the top. Put a little flour down on surface and roll dough into a round. Lay dough inside the pan and spoon on the filling. Make sure filling is level. Roll out remaining dough and place on top of the apple filling. Make sure dough completely covers the apples to the edges. 
4.	Place 9 inch spring form pan on a baking sheet lined with aluminum foil. Place baking sheet and Apple Tarte in oven. Bake at 325º for 1 hour 20 minutes or until top crust is golden. 
5.	Remove pan and set on top of surface. Cut into 8 pieces and serve warm right out of the pan or let it cool. When cool, remove round top of the pan, place onto a cake platter, cut and serve. Serve with whip cream or vanilla ice cream, warm or at room temperature.❌⭕️

2 sticks of butter
1 C of brown sugar
1/2 C of white sugar
2tbsp of vegetable oil
2 Eggs

2 3/4 -3 cups of Kamut Flour add about 1/4 more of all purpose ** add enough until dough is not sticking to bowl

1. Preheat oven to 350
2. Mix butter I use cold butter with sugars and vegetable oil
3. Add eggs, vanilla, salt, mix till combined
4. Add baking soda, baking powder, cornstarch, and add 1C of flour at a time until the dough is no longer sticking to the bowl.
5. Mix in white chocolate chips and crushed Biscoff cookies. 
6. Roll cookie dough into balls and place on a cookie sheet
( take out half way through and smash them down then continue to bake ) 
7. Bake for 9-10 minutes until slightly golden
8. Melt Biscoff cookie butter and drizzle over the top.

DAVID’S BAVARIAN STUFFED BAGUETTE PRETZELS

MAKES 6 mini baguette pretzels🥨 | TIME 1.5 hrs | BAKE 450˚

1 teaspoon sugar
4 teaspoons active dry yeast
1¾ cups warm water (between 100-110˚)
5 cups White Kamut flour
½ cup sugar
1½ teaspoons French gray coarse salt
1 Tablespoon canola or olive oil
1 Tablespoon honey
¼-½ cup warm water, if needed
For bath: ½ cup baking soda &
 4 cups hot tap water
French gray salt for sprinkling over pretzels

1- Put 1 teaspoon of sugar in a small bowl. Add yeast and 1¾ cups warm water. Stir gently.
Cover and let rise until foamy.
2- In a large bowl or electric mixer, add flour, sugar and salt. Mix. Add yeast mixture, oil and 
honey. Mix thoroughly with dough hook or wooden spoon. Add up to ½ cup more warm 
water as needed to get a firm dough consistency. Turn out onto lightly floured surface and 
knead by hand or with mixer for 7-8 minutes.
3 - Put a few drops of olive oil in a large bowl and place dough in it, turning over once. Cover 
with plastic sprayed with cooking spray. Let rise for 1 hour.
4 - Preheat oven to 450º 
Divide the dough into 6 so you can make 6 baguette pretzels !! Roll out the dough and place the filling down the middle and pinch up the dough to cover the filling !!!

5 - Spray a baking sheet with oil. In a 9x13 inch pan, mix 4 cups hot water and baking soda until 
dissolved. Immediately dunk each baguette pretzel into warm soda water. Let drip back into bowl for
2 seconds and place on baking sheet. Sprinkle with French gray coarse salt as desired. 

Place in oven and bake for 8 minutes on the bottom rack (or until golden brown), then brush on melted butter. Serve 
hot or place on cooling rack to cool.

Recipe for Dough 

2 1/4 cup white kamut flour (OR 2 1/2 cup all purpose)
2 Tbsp sugar 
1 tsp baking powder 
1/2 tsp baking soda
1 tsp salt
1/2 cup soft butter
1 cup milk
1/2 cup sourdough discard (right from fridge) 

Filling:
1/2 cup soft butter
1/2 cup sugar
1/2 cup brown sugar 
2 tsp cinnamon 

•mix all dry ingredients together
•add butter and gently cut in. 
•add milk and discard and combine to make a cohesive dough. 
•knead for 5 mins, adding any additional flour needed to make a soft dough. 
•leave to rise/ferment in bowl for 2-4 hours. 
•roll out on floured surface. 
•spread filling evenly beginning with butter and then sprinkling the sugars and cinnamon. 
•roll up as if you are making cinnamon rolls.
•beginning one inch in, divide the roll into three equal sections by slicing length wise from top to bottom (be sure to slice all the way through the roll with a sharp knife).
•braid the dough and wrap it into a circle.
•place in 10-12” cast iron pan, lined with parchment paper (don’t skip the parchment)
•bake at 350 for 35 mins (or up to 40 depending on the oven, watch it closely). 
•let cool and drizzle with icing! 

For icing:
1 cup icing sugar
1 tbsp salted butter
6-8 tbsp heavy cream
*blend adding enough cream to make it a pourable consistency.

Thai Chicken Pizza 🍕

Ingredients
Peanut Sauce:
1/4 cup balsamic vinegar
2 1/2 Tablespoons granulated sugar
2 Tablespoons brown sugar
2 Tablespoons soy sauce
1/2 teaspoon crushed red pepper
1/8 teaspoon coarse salt
1 fresh garlic clove crushed
2 Tablepsoons chunky peanut butter
2 pizza dough balls to make two 10 to 12 inches pizza; Tuscan Sun Pizza dough recipe page 133
2 Tablespoons olive oil
2 fresh garlic cloves crushed
1 cup chicken breasts cooked and torn into pieces or shredded
6 thin slices fresh Buffalo Mozzarella cheese
1/2 cup shredded Mozzarella cheese
1 1/2 Tablespoons shredded carrot
Sliced red onion to taste optional
1/4 cup cilantro leaves
1/2 cup whole peanuts

Directions
Pre-Heat over to 500 degrees
Prepare the dough for your pizza. Or use 2 frozen dough balls, thawed.
Prepare the Peanut Sauce:
In a small sauce pan over medium heat bring the vinegar, sugar, brown sugar, soy sauce, red pepper, salt and garlic to a boil stirring frequently.
Remove from heat. Whisk in the peanut butter. Set aside. Sauce must be slightly warm to spread on pizza.
Prepare the pizza dough:
Roll out your dough ball at a time. Place the dough on an oiled pizza pan or baking sheet. Or, on a pizza peel with a little flour and cornmeal to move pizza to a stone or tile.
Mix 2 Tablespoons olive oil in a small bowl with garlic. Brush the mixture over the entire pizza dough.
Spread on half the Peanut Sauce. Spread the chicken pieces around. Disperse the cheeses evenly. Sprinkle carrots and onion, if using. Bake in a 500 degree oven for 6-8 minutes on bottom oven rack until crisp. Remove from oven and sprinkle on the cilantro and peanuts.

These are the best brownies in the world! So chewy and beautiful. It took us a while to perfect it because the activity in the discard really makes a difference with this one! You need it nice and flat and you can’t over bake!! Like take them out even when there’s a bit of crumb on the toothpick and even if you feel they’re not fully done!, they will harden up while cooling and if you leave them too long they get can get cakey because of the discard. **do not over bake**
Also, make sure you use high quality milk chocolate and pour the caramel sauce over top, it is life changing!!!!

Sourdough brownie recipe:
1 cup butter (1/2 cup melted, 1/2 cup soft)
3 cups sugar
6 eggs 
1/2 cup sourdough discard 
1 Tbsp vanilla 
2 1/4 cups kamut  or 2 3/4 cups all purpose 
1 tsp baking powder 
1/2 tsp salt 
1/2 cup dutch processed cocoa powder (important!)
2 cups milk chocolate 

Caramel sauce:
3/4 cup packed brown sugar 
1/2 cup butter 
1/2 cup heavy cream

Brownies:
-stir together butter and sugar until well blended. Add discard, eggs and vanilla. Mix well.
-in separate bowl mix flour , baking powder, salt and cocoa. 
- blend dry ingredients into wet ingredients and stir until combined. Fold in chocolate.
- grease a 12x17 pan, spread batter into pan.
- bake at 350 for 30 mins. 

Sauce:
-combine sugar butter and cream in a saucepan and cook over medium heat until butter melts. Stir occasionally. Simmer 15 mins. 
-let cool (it will thicken more) pour over baked brownies.

Raspberry Sweet Buns (With David’s Pretzel Dough Recipe)

Dough
	•	1/2 tsp White sugar
	•	2 tsp Red Star active dry yeast
	•	3/4 cups Warm water between 100-110 degrees
	•	2.5 Cups Kamut white flour
	•	1/4 Cup White sugar
	•	1/2 tsp Fleur del Sel or French Gray Salt
	•	1/2tbsp Canola Oil
	•	2 tbsp honey
Filling
1 cup (4 oz) fresh or frozen raspberries (1 small package)
1/3 cup brown sugar
3 tbsp unsalted room temp butter

Glaze
2 cups powdered sugar
3 tbsp milk
1 tsp vanilla extract

Directions
1.	Put 1/2 teaspoon of sugar in a small bowl. Add yeast and 3/4 cups warm water. Stir gently. Cover and let rise until foamy.
2.	In a large bowl or electric mixer, add flour, sugar and salt. Mix. Add yeast mixture, oil and honey. Mix thoroughly with dough hook or wooden spoon. Add up to ½ cup more warm water as needed to get a firm dough consistency. Turn out onto lightly floured surface and knead by hand or with mixer for 7-8 minutes.
3.	Let rise for 1 hour.
4.	Make the filling by putting the raspberries in a saucepan. Smash and cook to release the juices. Cook 3-4 minutes until most of the water has evaporated and it’s a thicker paste. Let cool completely and then smash in the butter and sugar.
	5.	Roll the dough out into a big rectangle and divide into 12 pieces.
	6.	Roll each pieces into a thin rectangle and spread with a thin layer of filling.
	7.	Roll up from the long way and cut in half lengthwise leaving the top connected.
	8.	Twist and place in a greased muffin tin, wrapping around and then tucking the tail in the middle.
	9.	Repeat with all pieces of dough.
	10.	Brush with egg wash from a beaten egg and bake at 375F (190C) for 15-17 minutes.
	11.	Make the glaze by whisking together the powdered sugar, milk, and vanilla. 
12.	Drizzle over the cooled buns and enjoy!

Want the fastest cinnamon roll baguettes or even make cinnamon rolls 🤤🥖 you will have these in 30 mins and they are insane 💥💯 

Recipe :

3 cups warm (105-115 degrees water, divided)
3 tablespoons active dry yeast
4 teaspoons sugar (divided)
4 1/2 cups all-purpose Kamut flour 
2 teaspoons French salt

Make the filling :
1/2 cup sugar 
1/2 cup brown sugar 
2 tsp cinnamon 

1 stick of butter soften to spread on the 4 baguettes 

Icing : 
1 tablespoon of softened butter 
1 cup of powder sugar 
6-8 tablespoons heavy cream ( keep adding cream to get your desired consistency) 

1- In a small bow, combine 1 cup of the water, the yeast, and 2 teaspoon of the sugar. Stir just to combine and cover with plastic wrap or a plate. Let the mixture stand about 5 minutes or until bubble or foamy.

2-In a large mixing bowl or the bowl of heavy-duty mixer or food processor, blend the flour, salt, the remaining 2 teaspoon of sugar, and the yeast mixture. Gradually add water, up to the remaining 1 cup, and mix until the dough forms a smooth ball that is not too sticky to handle. (If the dough ends up too sticky, add a little more Kamut flour.) Turn the dough onto a floured surface and knead briefly, until the dough is smooth and elastic.

3- Cut the dough in half and shape the halves into 4 baguettes. Roll out with a rolling pin , spread on some butter and the cinnamon / sugar mixture !!!! Then roll up the baguette and put into your greased  baguette pans ( these are our own Food Nanny Pans more coming soon💯💯💯💯💯💯 ) and place the loaves in the pan. 

Score 3 slits down the baguette , cover with a dish towel, and let rise in a warm place about 20 minutes, or until doubled in bulk.

Bake at 450 degrees for 15-20 mins until the bottoms are light brown !!!!! Put your baguette pans on a cookie sheet so it didn’t spill out in your oven !!!!!!

Brioche:
1⁄4 cup milk
2 tbsp granulated sugar
4 tsp active yeast
2 1/4 Kamut or 3 cups (400g) all purpose flour
4 large eggs, room temp
1 tsp salt
14 tbsp salted butter, cubed, soft but still a little cold

*You can add the chocolate chips into the dough now or the other way 
1 beaten egg + a pinch of salt for the tops before baking 

Heat up the milk until tepid (7-10 secs in the microwave). Make sure it is no more than 100F (37C). Add the sugar and yeast then whisk to combine. Let sit about 5-10 minutes until the yeast foams to make sure it is active and thriving.

In a stand mixer bowl, add the eggs, then the yeast mixture. On top of this pour in the flour and salt. Mix together with a spoon to form a shaggy dough then pop on the mixer. Use the dough hook and mix on low speed until it attaches to the bread hook.

Increase the speed to low-medium (speed 4 on KA) and mix for 3 to 5 minutes or until smooth.

Jill’s Gingerbread Men

Ingredients 
1 cup butter
1 cup sugar
1 cup molasses 
1 egg
2 TBSP white vinegar
1 1/2 tsp baking soda
1/2 tsp salt
1 tsp ground cinnamon 
1 tsp ground cloves
1 TBSP ground ginger 
5 cups of all purpose flour (plus 2TBSP at high elevation)
Or 4 2/3 cups Kamut Flour 🙌🏻

Cream butter, sugar and molasses together. Add the egg and vinegar and mix. Stir in the dry ingredients until the dough comes together. 

Form the dough into two discs and wrap in plastic wrap. Chill in the fridge for 3 hours or freezer for 30 minutes. 

When you’re ready to bake, preheat the over to 375 (350 convection). Roll out the dough about 1/4 thick and cut into shapes. Place on a parchment-lined baking sheet. Bake 6-8 minutes. This will vary depending on the size of the cookie and your oven. The cookies are done when they puff slightly and start to crack, and when you touch them lightly with your finger the cookie springs back. Do not let the cookies brown on the bottom or they will be crunchy.

When the baking is done, slide the parchment paper (with cookies on it) off of the cookie sheet and onto a cooling rack. 

For the icing, I mix about 4 cups of powdered sugar and about 3 TBSP of milk together to form the glaze. It’s never exact and the amount of milk varies every time, and it’s really easy to add too much milk, so take it easy and just add a little at a time until you get the right consistency.

Hold each gingerbread cookie and dip the top into the bowl of icing. Use an offset spatula or the flat side of a knife to scrape off extra icing and leave a nice smooth surface. Place the cookies back on the parchment to allow the icing time to set up. After about an hour you can stack the cookies.

Keep the cookies in an airtight container. They stay soft and delicious for several days.

3 tablespoons active dry yeast
4 teaspoons sugar (divided)
4 1/2 cups all-purpose Kamut flour 
2 teaspoons French salt

Make the filling :
1/2 cup sugar 
1/2 cup brown sugar 
2 tsp cinnamon 

1 stick of butter soften 

Icing : 
1 tablespoon of softened butter 
1 cup of powder sugar 
6-8 tablespoons heavy cream ( keep adding cream to get your desired consistency) 

1- In a small bow, combine 1 cup of the water, the yeast, and 2 teaspoon of the sugar. Stir just to combine and cover with plastic wrap or a plate. Let the mixture stand about 5 minutes or until bubble or foamy.

2-In a large mixing bowl or the bowl of heavy-duty mixer or food processor, blend the flour, salt, the remaining 2 teaspoon of sugar, and the yeast mixture. Gradually add water, up to the remaining 1 cup, and mix until the dough forms a smooth ball that is not too sticky to handle. (If the dough ends up too sticky, add a little more Kamut flour.) Turn the dough onto a floured surface and knead briefly, until the dough is smooth and elastic.

3- divide the dough in half ! Roll out one section of the dough like you would making cinnamon rolls . Place the dough on parchment paper! Spread the softened butter and then sprinkle the cinnamon & sugar on top ! Roll out the other dough and place on top ! Make into a heart like in the video and cut into strips and twist !!!

4- bake 450 on a cookie sheet or pizza stone until light brown on the bottoms !!! Around 15 mins ! 

Take out and when cooled put icing 😋 and enjoy !!!!
